# Project Guide: Geometrik AI Course Platform

## Project Overview
The Geometrik AI Course platform is a modern educational website built with Next.js, React 19, and Tailwind CSS. It features course curriculum, instructor profiles, community sections, pricing plans, FAQ section, and a Case Studies section showcasing student projects.

## Key Features
- Curriculum presentation with clear progression paths
- Instructor profiles showcasing faculty expertise
- Community engagement features
- Transparent pricing and enrollment options
- FAQ section for common questions
- Case Studies showcase of successful student projects
- Responsive design for all devices

## Development Guidelines
- Follow atomic design principles for component organization
- Use server components where possible for data fetching
- Implement animations with Framer Motion, especially for the Case Studies feature
- Use Markdown files for case study content
- Maintain consistent design language across all sections

## Case Studies Implementation
- Store case study content as Markdown files in `/content/case-studies/`
- Create listing page and detail page using dynamic routes
- Develop card components based on existing `FeatureCard` component
- Implement staggered animations for card entry and hover effects
- Create detailed view with metrics, content sections, and visual elements

## Tech Stack Highlights
- Next.js 15.1.0 with App Router
- React 19
- TypeScript 5.x
- Tailwind CSS 3.4.x
- Framer Motion 12.0.0-alpha.0
- Markdown processing with gray-matter, remark, and rehype

## Directory Structure
- `/app`: Next.js pages and layouts
- `/components`: Reusable UI components
- `/content`: Markdown files for static content
- `/lib`: Utility functions and shared logic
- `/public`: Static assets

This rule provides guidance on the project's purpose, structure, and development patterns.
